#  MiniWeb — A Minimal Python Web Framework

MiniWeb is a lightweight educational web framework built from scratch to help beginners understand the **core concepts of backend development** without relying on large frameworks like Flask or Django.

This project teaches:

- How HTTP requests work 
![HTTP work](assets/HTTP%20protocol.jpeg)
 
- How routing works internally  
- How web frameworks parse headers, bodies, and query parameters 
![HTTP request](assets/Screenshot%202025-11-27%20at%2014-36-33%20HTTP%20Requests%20Methods%20Headers%20and%20Bodies.png) 
- How servers handle sockets and connections  
- How responses are structured  
1[HTTP response](assets/HTTP_ResponseMessageExample.png)

Perfect for students, backend beginners, and anyone preparing to build more advanced projects.

---

##  Features

- ✔️ Simple routing system (`@app.route("/")`)
- ✔️ Manual HTTP request parsing (method, URL, headers, body)
- ✔️ Query parameter extraction (`?name=Rayane`)
- ✔️ Form data parsing (`POST` forms)
- ✔️ Clean Response object system
- ✔️ Beginner-friendly architecture

---

